rComments: Knows the topic of Post-war Germany very well, a very note intensive course as she doesn't post lecture slides just outlines, wants her class to do well and gives information on what to know

Good Professor to teach a Holocaust class. She really knows her stuff, and actually looks like she loves to teach and help her students understand. She will help you if you ask her for help, go to her office hours rather than email. She does have a funny side which rarely comes out. Grades fair, and over all very nice.

Probably one of the best profs at UTM. She makes lectures engaging by noting out the opposing points of view for every topic. You will definitely leave every lecture with an opinion on the topic. She expects a lot from essays, but if you were as interested in the course as I was, then you will have no problem putting enough work into your paper.
good lectures, very interesting. she makes the class more interesting because of her passion for the subjects
her lectures are SO interesting. she's apparently one of the worlds top experts on WW2. very insightful, though her tests are sometimes hard. tutorial gives you an easy 20%

Fairly good prof who teaches an interesting course. Clear lecturer. Tests or assignments aren't hard but don't expect an A unless you're a good writer. Decent amount of reading but not above avg for a history course.

Teaches a course on the Holocaust during WWII, and consistently proves that she knows the topic very well.I was extremely grateful for the lack of pictures used during the course, because the topic is gruesome enough. Professor Wittmann is exceptionally unhelpful when if comes to student questions about the course. Poor TA choice as well.
